      <h2 id="fabricjs">Get started with Fabric JS</h2>
      <p>
         <span>Use the CDN, Bower, NPM, or Nuget to get the components and core styling.</span>.
      </p>
      <ol class="steps">
         <li>
            <p>The easiest way to get Fabric is by referencing the CDN. Include the following in the @HEAD of your page:</p>
            <div class="codeBlock isLightTheme">
               <div class="code">
                  <pre>
                     <code class="bash hljs">&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;https://static2.sharepointonline.com/files/fabric/office-ui-fabric-js/1.2.0/css/fabric.min.css&quot;&gt;<br />&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;https://static2.sharepointonline.com/files/fabric/office-ui-fabric-js/1.2.0/css/fabric.components.min.css&quot;&gt;<br />&lt;script src=&quot;https://static2.sharepointonline.com/files/fabric/office-ui-fabric-js/1.2.0/js/fabric.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code>
                  </pre>
               </div>
            </div>
            <p>To reference the latest version, just change the version number in the URL to your desired version. All versions of Fabric are on the CDN, and the latest version is @TODO: ADD VERSION NUMBER DYNAMICALLY.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Copy the HTML from one of the samples into your page. For example with the button</p>
            <div class="codeBlock isLightTheme">
               <div class="code">
                  <pre>
                     <code class="bash hljs">&lt;button class=&quot;ms-Button&rdquo;&gt;<br />&lt;span class=&quot;ms-Button-label&quot;&gt;Create Account&lt;/span&gt;<br />&lt;/button&gt;</code>
                  </pre>
               </div>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Add the appropriate &lt;script&gt; tag to your page below the references to Fabric's JavaScript to instantiate, for example, all the Button components on the page:
            </p>
            <div class="codeBlock isLightTheme">
               <div class="code">
                  <pre>
                     <code class="bash hljs">&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;
var ButtonElements = document.querySelectorAll(&quot;.ms-Button&quot;);
for(var i = 0; i &lt; ButtonElements.length; i++) {
new fabric['Button'](ButtonElements[i], function() {
// Insert Event Here
});
}
&lt;/script&gt;
</code>
                  </pre>
               </div>
            </div>
            <p>Fabric’s JavaScript is lightweight and simple. You can extend, gut, or use what’s included as-is.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>You can also reference styles from Fabric Core, such as the type styles:</p>
            <div class="codeBlock isLightTheme">
               <div class="code">
                  <pre>
                     <code class="bash hljs">&lt;span class=&quot;ms-font-su ms-fontColor-themePrimary&quot;&gt;Big blue text&lt;/span&gt;</code>
                  </pre>
               </div>
            </div>
            <p>For more information on assets and styles available in Fabric Core, check out the <a href="https://dev.office.com/fabric#/styles">Styles documentation</a>.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
